Source: this file is NOT vendored; the declarations under
`prism_supplement.rbs` are Rigor-authored supplements to the
`prism` gem's own bundled RBS (under the gem's `sig/` tree).
The gem's `sig/` is loaded automatically via
`Rigor::Environment::DEFAULT_LIBRARIES` (entry `"prism"`); this
overlay adds only declarations the gem's RBS omits (today: the
`ParseResult#attach_comments!` / `#mark_newlines!` Ruby methods
and the C-extension-bound `StringQuery.{local?, constant?,
method_name?}` singleton methods).

The supplement is written from scratch; no upstream RBS is
vendored here. The prism gem itself is licensed MIT (see
https://github.com/ruby/prism/blob/main/LICENSE.md) and the
Ruby-source method signatures are facts of the gem's public
API, not copyrightable expression.
